Thomas COOKE of Braintree, Essex
Six titles published from 1722 to 1739 in London.
British Library.

"Albion; or, the Court of Neptune. A masque. [By Thomas Cooke.]"  1724.
"The Eunuch, or, the Darby captain, a farce, etc"  1737.
"Marlborough, a poem, in three cantos. Occasion'd by the death of the late Duke of Marlborough"
1722.
"The Bays Miscellany, or Colley “ 1730.
 "The Mournful Nuptials, or Love the cure of all woes, a tragedy.” 1739.
"The Triumphs of Love and Honour, a play ... [In verse.] “ 1731.
